Regarding Comment #2, VE doesnt understand method argument parent's like 
---------------
private void createDialogWindow(Shell parentShell) {
...
dialogWindow = new Shell(parentShell, SWT.APPLICATION_MODAL |
SWT.DIALOG_TRIM);
...
}
-----------------

You would need something like
---------------
private void createDialogWindow() {
...
dialogWindow = new Shell(parentShell, SWT.APPLICATION_MODAL |
SWT.DIALOG_TRIM);
...
}
-----------------

However, you can drop a Shell on the freeform and select the option 'Change parent..' to select the global Shell for which this should be a dialog of. The only problem with that is that it visually shows the new dialog Shell as a child of the parent Shell in the treeviewer and graphical viewer. A quick getaround for this is to not set the parent till all UI editing is finished and finally set the parent.

Other than that I was able to create dialogs and save/reopen in 	I20051216 build.
